column2: Some particles in water- brownish tinge
Some rain- 2 days ago.  Partly cloudy.
Almost no particles in lake- water is calm.
No particles- rain during the week- 2.3 inches.  North winds at 5 mph.
High thin clouds- no particles in water.
Winds are calm- sky is clear.
Sky: high thin clouds (no break)- wind: 5-10 mph from west.
Sky- is clear.  Wind- is 5-10 mph from northeast.  Particles in the water- anchor came up full of brown silt.
Wind is south @ 10 mph- sky is clear- no particles in the water- anchor came up clean.
Sky is clear- wind @ 10 mph northeast- no particles in the water- I thought the disk was clearer- deeper- but a moment later the reading changed.
Sky- high thin clouds- wind- 10 mph- west- particles in water- when pulling up the anchor- I noticed a flurry of brown silt.
Sky is clear- wind is 10-15 mph from north.
Clear sky- calm winds- a chunk of mud on anchor.

Many more weeds than two weeks ago. a few particles suspended in water. anchor flukes came up with woody-like sludge. sky mostly clear with puffy clouds coming in. no wind - calm. loon gave warning call as eagle flew over.
Clear sky- S wind 0-5 mph- no particles in water- anchor came up clean- 1.72" of rain in last 4 days
Clear sky- W wind 5-10 mph- particles in water- along with chunks of weeds- anchor came up with muck
Mostly sunny- air temp 48 F. fluffy white clouds. sunny. hit bottom at 18 feet.
Summer clouds building on horizon- air temp at 7 am 56 F.
Calm wind- clear sky- anchor full of muck-weedy- green clumps in water 1/8" by  5/4" in size
Wind is south @ 5 mph- sky has high thin clouds- anchor has muck on flukes.
Skies are clear- temp is 50 degrees @ 7 am- breezy- 0.25" of rain yesterday afternoon.
West wind 20 mph. clear sky at time of secchi.
Clear sky- wind south 0-5 mph- particles in water.
Wind from south- 5 mph.  Sky-test during break in clouds.  Anchor came up with muck on flukes.
Test during break in clouds. W wind 10 mph.
West wind 10 mph.  Test during break in clouds.  Anchor came up full of northern milfoil and sludge.
Wind is 5 mph from the west
Sky clear- wind 10 mph.  Adult loon feeding single baby loon (1/2 size adult).  Anchor full of weeds and woody sludge.
Clear sky.  West wind 5 mph.  Anchor full of weeds and fibrous-like sludge.
Clear sky- west wind 15 mph.  Anchor came up with fibrous sludge and weeds.
Very slight haze- calm and no particles. calm water. clear skies- but hazy.
Clear sky- north wind- 10 mph- sludge on anchor.
Clear sky- wind is calm- sludge on anchor.
Sky is clear- SW wind 5 mph- anchor came up with full at weeds- no sludge- received 4.65" rain in the last 4 days.
Clear sky- calm winds- anchor came up full of sludge and weeds.  Hard to find deep hole.
Clear sky- SW wind @ 5 mph- anchor came up clean- further out spot. water cold!!
High thin haze- bright sun- slight breeze to calm.  High clouds- temp is 45 degrees at 8 am- 52 @ 10 am
Bright- hazy- breeze coming up.  Ice out 4-21. bright hazy- air 45 F at 7am. wind calm. pair of eagles- one carrying a fish flew over- calling as they approached nest at SE corner of lake.
2.3" rain since last test on 5/6/95.  Sludge on anchor fluke- south wind 15 mph- clear sky.
Wind north 5-10 mph- sky high thin clouds- rain 0.14" since last week.
Clear sky- north wind 5-10 mph- sludge on anchor- 0.14" rain since last test- barn swallow nests under bridge between gull and Falk lakes.
Wind N 5-10 mph- test between clouds- 1" rain since last test.
High thin clouds- south wind 5 mph- sludge on anchor fluke- no rain in two weeks- barn swallows in nests under bridge.
High thin clouds- west wind 5-10 mph- no rain since last week- sludge on anchor fluke.
Sky high thin clouds- wind north 5 mph- sludge on anchor flukes- 2.25" rain since 7/7/95.
Small high clouds building in the northwest- winds are calm- secchi test taken during a large break in the clouds.2.5 inches rain from 7/7/95 through 7/16/95.
Clear sky- west wind 10 mph- 0.50" rain in last 24 hours +1.10" since 7/14/95.
Rain 7.85" since 7/28/95- sky clear- wind west 10 mph.
Sludge on anchor flukes when pulled in.
42 F at 8am. cloudy all morning- yesterday same. Bright moonlit night. very windy last few days. Sludge on anchor flukes.
35 degrees at 7 AM.  51 degrees at 1 PM.
Clear sky. W wind 15 mph.  Lake level: very high
Clear sky. west wind 5 mph. sludge on anchor flukes. green particles in water (1/8" diameter).
Clear sky. calm water. green particles in water (1/4" diameter + larger).
5" rain two days ago. Reading varies from under-current. Sludge on anchor flukes. Clear sky. W wind 10 mph.
Clear sky. calm water. sludge on anchor flukes.  Lake level: very high
Clear sky. calm - no wind. sludge on anchor flukes. 10" rain in last month.  Lake level: very high
Clarity depth changing during test. clear sky. north winds 5-10 mph.
4 young swallows in nest under bridge between Falk Lake + Gull Lake.
Southwest wind 5-10 mph- clear sky. great blue heron flew over to shore on W side.
2.5 inches of rain from 4 AM to 9 AM 7/25/97.
High thin clouds- W wind 5 mph.
Sky is clear- south wind at 10 mph- water level was high
Calm- clear sky- 2 chick + 2 adult loons.
Clear sky- calm winds- cold water.
Calm (lee).  High thin clouds.  Sludge on anchor flukes.
Test between clouds. west wind 5-10 mph. air temperature in low 40s (cold hands).
Clear sky- north wind at 5-10 mph- mud on anchor fluke.
With grand niece- Hannah Vanwetter (age 7 1/2)- clear sky- west wind at 5 mph- mud on anchor flukes.
Clear sky- west wind at 10 mph.
South wind at 10 mph and clear sky.
North wind at 10 mph- clear sky between clouds- and mud on anchor flukes.
South wind at 10 mph- clear sky- and mud on anchor shaft.
Monitored with grand nephew- Sam Vanwetter.  Calm and clear sky.
Calm- clear sky- adult and baby loon nearby- and mud on anchor flukes.
Calm- clear sky- and mud on the anchor flukes.
Calm- clear sky- and mud on the anchor flukes.
North wind 10-15 mph. Clear between clouds. One loon diving.
South wind 5 mph. Clear- hazy sky. Hot and humid.
East wind 0-5 mph. Clear sky. Mud on anchor flukes.
Clear sky. Calm. Particles in water.
Clear sky- south wind 0-10 mph. 5.5" rain during last week.
DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
Reading corrected for 4 ft rail on pontoon.
West wind 10 mph.  Clear skies.  Mud on anchor flukes.  Over 2" rain in past week.  Rail correction.
South wind 5 mph.  Clear sky.  Rail correction.
Wind calm.  Clear sky.  15 turtles sunning on log.  Rail correction (4 ft). Data collectors: Kent Dickerman and Marshall Thompson- Bliane Darrah and Toni Ventenbergs.
South wind 5 mph; clear sky.  10 turtles sunning on log.  Rail correction 4 ft.
Loon- turtles- barn swallows.  Wind SW 5 mph.  Test between clouds.  Rail correction 4 ft.  Data collectors: Kent Dickerman and Walker Sampson- Isabella- Jesse- Jared- John- Chris.
Loon and chick.  5 turtles.  Soaring immature eagle.  Clear sky- south wind 5 mph.  Mud on anchor flukes.  Green back heron.  Rail correction.
Calm- high thin clouds.  Ducks swimming.  Green particles and chunks in water.  4 ft rail correction to surface.
DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
West wind 10 mph.  Test between clouds.  Mud on anchor flukes.
Clear sky.  South wind 10 mph.  Clera sky.  Mud on anchor flukes.  Geese swimming - 8 adults- 12 goslings.
Clera sky- E wind 10 mph.  Geese swimming: 6 adults and 17 goslings.
Clear sky; 5 mph wind.  Loon with baby on back.  Didn't dive when boat was 10 ft away.  Baby hidden.
Calm- clear sky.   Two loons with two babies.
South winds.  10-15 mph.  High thin clouds.
36 geese.  Mud and weeds on anchor fluke.  Test between clouds.  Pair of loons - 1 young turning light brown.
South wind 10 mph.  Clear sky.  Green globs in water.  Loon teaching young to fish.  Mud on anchor flukes.
Clear sky- calm- mud on flukes of anchor.  Single loon.  Local song birds gone.
slight breeze- recent rain- Mark Bixby helper
clear and cool. Mark Bixby helper
high clouds- fair- Mark Bixby helper
warm and sunny- Mark Bixby helper warm and sunny-recent rain-  Mark Bixby helper
It had been a delayed spring. Overnight rain had left a clear breezy day- with scattered clouds- the temp was 65 degrees F. Beaufort 3
Mark Bixby was my helper. It was a windy day.
Mark Bixby was my helper. It was a windy day.
Hot summer day- a bit hazy because of wildfires to west- still. Some boat activity. Accompanied by Mark Bixby and Tina Juliana and Angel Hillstrom
Scattered clouds- calm- 895 degrees- Mark Bixby is my my helper.
Scattered cirrostratus clouds- light breeze High haze- light breeze- scattered cirrostratus clouds
Moderate wind- scattered cumulus clouds- occasional cirrostratus clouds Moderate wind- scattered cumulus clouds- occasional serostratus clouds
Light breeze from SW- rare cirrus clouds Light breeze from the southwest- rare cirrus clouds
Light breeze- air temp 70- surface water temp 66
Scattered clouds- breezy Clear and breezy
